    "For the inorganic P form, 102 models with a mean accuracy of 68.23 % and a cross-validation score of 0.58 were selected (Figs. 4 and S13).",
    "The variables with higher values of MDA for the inorganic P form were total N, sand, total organic C, MAT, latitude, and clay (Fig. 7).",
    "Total N, total organic C, and clay presented positive relations with inorganic P; in contrast, MAT and sand showed negative relations (Fig. S14).",
    "For the occluded P form, 56 models were selected and presented a mean accuracy of 64.6 % with a score of 0.58 in the crossvalidation (Fig. S15).",
    "The most important variables for the prediction of occluded P were pH, sand, TN, clay, silt, and latitude (Fig. 7)."
